                            </div>                       &nbsp;
                            <p>Shampoo, when lathered with water, is a surfacant, which, while cleaning the hair and scalp, can <strong>remove the natural oils (sebum) which lubricate the hair shaft.</strong></p>
                            <p>Shampooing is frequently followed by conditioners which increase the ease of combing and styling.</p>
                            <p>Shampoo cleans by stripping sebum from the hair.</p>
