                <br>
                <p>SPECT scans are primarily used to diagnose and track the progression of diseases such as heart disease, bone disorders, gall bladder and even intestinal bleeding. Recent studies suggest that SPECT agents can also aid in diagnosing Parkinson’s disease in the brain. </p>


